      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's actually kinda crazy to think about. the \"deliberately concealed\" part makes so much sense because whenever i bring up my great-grandfather, my parents just shut down or change the subject. there was also this old velvet box in the trunk with a map of a coastline i don't recognize, and a letter written in a weird, stylized script. if this was an esoteric lineage, like you said, what kind of groups or dynasties would have used a symbol like a hawk and a broken compass? it feels like they were meant to be travelers or explorers who didn't follow the standard rules.",
